In line with the ongoing N-POWER Batch C online application which commenced Friday June 26, 2020, the Ministry of Humanitarian Affairs Disaster Management and Social Development, hereby announces that over 1,000,000 applications have been received from across the Federation in less than 48 hours. The Deputy Director of Information, FMHADMSD, Rhoda Ishaku Iliya said in a press statement that after the Honourable Minister, Sadiya Umar Farouq, declared open the new N-Power Portal on the Ministry’s website on npower.fmhds.gov.ng, the Ministry wishes to reiterate that all young Nigerians between the ages of 18-35 with or without formal education can apply for a slot in the new program which would be very focused on agriculture. According to the statement, the number of applications so far received is an indication of the number of our youths who need jobs and have confidence in the program that the Ministry will continue to collaborate with its technical partners to provide timely support to all applicants. “The selection process would be fair and transparent and the public would also be carried along at every stage. “The Ministry will like to assure Nigerians that the N-Power portal is secured and no data has been compromised, adding that the portal is open for all Nigerians who meet the application criteria”. 